---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import BreadcrumbNav from "@/components/BreadcrumbNav.astro";
import summary from "@/data/summary.json";
---

<Layout title="About" description="About this site, data provenance, and license.">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-8 pb-16">
    <BreadcrumbNav crumbs={[{ label: "Home", href: "/" }, { label: "About" }]} />
    <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink-900">About</h1>

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-5 text-[14.5px] text-ink-700 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        This is an independent, open-source visualization of Harvey AI's
        <a class="underline decoration-ink-300 hover:decoration-accent-500" href="https://github.com/harveyai/harvey-labs" target="_blank" rel="noopener">harvey-labs</a>
        legal agent benchmark. The goal is to make it easy to see what kinds of legal work the benchmark covers and to look at the actual tasks, rubrics, and reference materials that an agent is graded against.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every task page reads its data from the upstream repository pinned at a specific commit, so links and contents stay stable between data refreshes. Reference documents are not redistributed here. Each file links back to its original location on GitHub.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-[20px] font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink-900 mt-8">Data provenance</h2>
      <ul class="text-[14px] space-y-1 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>Source: <a class="underline decoration-ink-300 hover:decoration-accent-500" href={`https://github.com/${summary.upstreamRepo}/tree/${summary.upstreamSha}`} target="_blank" rel="noopener">{summary.upstreamRepo}@{summary.upstreamSha.slice(0, 8)}</a></li>
        <li>License of upstream data: MIT (see the upstream <a class="underline decoration-ink-300 hover:decoration-accent-500" href="https://github.com/harveyai/harvey-labs/blob/main/LICENSE" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LICENSE</a>)</li>
        <li>Last data refresh: <span class="font-mono">{new Date(summary.generatedAt).toISOString().slice(0, 10)}</span></li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="font-display text-[20px] font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink-900 mt-8">How this site is built</h2>
      <p>
        At build time, a script walks the vendored copy of the benchmark, validates every task.json against a Zod schema, and emits one static page per task plus an index for listings and search. The interactive bits (rubric collapse, list filters) ship as small React islands inside an otherwise zero-JavaScript page.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-[20px] font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink-900 mt-8">Attribution</h2>
      <p>
        This site is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by Harvey AI. "Harvey", "BigLaw Bench", and related marks belong to their respective owners.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
